'''''Herald''''' was a [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttle]] used by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

According to the plan by [[Crix Madine/Legends|Crix Madine]] and the [[Sullustan/Legends|Sullustan]] technicians who had just joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance]], they needed a warhead in order to destroy the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Invincible (Strike Fear)|''Invincible'']] and end Operation Strike Fear. The Rebels soon learned about a new warhead being transferred from [[Celanon/Legends|Celanon]] to a deep space transfer zone by the [[BFF-1 bulk freighter/Legends|BFF-1 bulk freighter]] ''[[Gafra]]'' and planned to attack it at its destination.

An initial Rebel attack left the ''Gafra'' damaged and stranded before withdrawing. However, the freighter was still protected by a field of [[Space mine/Legends|mines]] around it. [[Keyan Farlander/Legends|Keyan Farlander]] in a Y-wing cleared them out and disabled the freighter. When that was done, the ''Herald'' came and boarded the freighter. Imperial [[Delta-class DX-9 stormtrooper transport|transports]] came and attempted to destroy the freighter before it could fall into enemy hands, but Farlander was able to drive them off.

With the help of abducted [[Cygnus Spaceworks/Legends|Cygnus Corp]] staff, the warhead was then delivered to the ''Invincible'' in a shuttle modified to appear to be an Imperial vessel, and the Star Destroyer was blown up from the inside.

